sequenceDiagram
    autonumber
    actor U as "User / Client"
    participant CA as "Channel Adapter"
    participant GW as "API Gateway"
    participant AR as "Agent Router"
    participant BA as "Selected Business Agent / Main Agent"
    participant SA as "Sub Agent"
    participant P as "SensePedia Core / LLM Planner"
    participant PV as "PlanValidator"
    participant E as "SensePedia Core / Graph Executor"
    participant MS as "Memory Service"
    participant KI as "Knowledge Infrastructure"
    participant LLM as "LLM Gateway"
    participant TR as "Tool Registry"
    participant TX as "Tool / Skill Executor"
    participant HO as "HostOps API"
    participant PI as "Pi Runtime"
    participant EXT as "External Systems (DB / Milvus / MinIO / Web)"
    participant OB as "Observability (LangFuse / Metrics / Logs)"

    U->>CA: Send request (message / API)
    CA->>GW: Normalize + Auth context
    GW->>AR: Route decision request
    alt Router mode = single_agent
        AR->>AR: Bind fixed agent (for example legal_agent)
    else Router mode = configured_routing
        AR->>AR: Apply tenant / channel / capability rules
    else Router mode = dynamic_routing
        AR->>AR: Evaluate rules + intent + fallback
    end
    AR->>BA: Forward request + routing context

    opt Runtime multi-agent enabled for this request
        BA->>SA: SubAgentCall(goal + scoped context)
        SA-->>BA: Partial result + evidence refs
    end

    BA->>P: Ask to plan within agent scope

    opt Recall durable memory / user prefs
        P->>MS: Recall(thread_id, user_id)
        MS-->>P: Memory context
    end

    opt Use shared knowledge capabilities
        P->>KI: Capability check / retrieve primitives
        KI-->>P: Available tools + constraints
    end

    P->>LLM: Request structured plan (ExecutionPlan schema)
    LLM-->>P: Structured plan candidate
    P->>PV: Validate(plan + agent scope + limits)
    PV->>TR: Check tool existence + auth scope + deps
    TR-->>PV: Tool metadata
    PV-->>P: Approved plan / validation errors
    P->>E: Submit validated plan + initial state

    loop For each task (serial or parallel)
        E->>TR: Resolve tool + policy
        TR-->>E: Tool binding (impl + schema)
        alt Task targets HostOps
            E->>HO: Execute hostops action
            HO->>PI: Run exec / ssh / files action
            PI-->>HO: Result / pending approval / error
            HO-->>E: Normalized hostops result
        else Task targets local skill or shared tool
            par Execute tool and trace
                E->>TX: Execute(tool, params)
                TX->>EXT: Call external dependency
                EXT-->>TX: Result / error
                TX-->>E: Tool result
            and
                E->>OB: Emit spans + events
            end
        end
        opt Checkpoint / state snapshot
            E->>MS: Persist checkpoint + summary
            MS-->>E: Ack
        end
    end

    E-->>BA: Final answer + citations / artifacts
    BA-->>GW: Response (optionally streaming)
    GW-->>CA: Deliver
    CA-->>U: Show answer
